<h2>Harbourfront</h2>
<figure class="post__image post__image--left"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/lake-shore_wm.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/responsive/lake-shore_wm-xs.jpg 300w ,https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/responsive/lake-shore_wm-sm.jpg 480w ,https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/responsive/lake-shore_wm-md.jpg 768w"  alt="" width="3096" height="4128"></figure>
<p>One of the best things to do on a hot summer day in Toronto is to wander near the Lake Ontario, among the joggers, dog-walkers and tourists enjoying the sun.</p>
<p>Going westwards along the lake, you will enter <a href="https://www.toronto.ca/data/parks/prd/facilities/complex/1707/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Toronto Music Garden</a>, near the marina. This peaceful little garden, filled with birds, butterflies and gorgeous plants, is ideal for an evening stroll.</p>
<figure class="post__image post__image--wide"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/lake-shore-2_wm.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 100vw" srcset="https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/responsive/lake-shore-2_wm-xs.jpg 300w ,https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/responsive/lake-shore-2_wm-sm.jpg 480w ,https://kindglobetrotter.github.io/media/posts/1/responsive/lake-shore-2_wm-md.jpg 768w"  alt="" width="6560" height="2416"></figure>
<h2>City Centre</h2>
<p>Toronto is a multicultural city, which perfectly combines new buildings with older architecture. Near the lake, the CN Tower and the skyscrappers are a constant reminder that the city centre is built to reach high altitudes.</p>
<p>However, among this extremely urban landscape, there is place for pieces of architecture that could belong in any European city's old town.</p>
